MissionCommands.Message: Welcome onboard on Apollo 13, where the journey towards the Moon continues as the crew prepares the cockpit for orbit.
Apollo 13, Houston. Your preliminary orbit down here is 102.5 times 100.3, and everything is looking good.
Roger, Houston. And it looks good to be up here again.
I'll bet.
Let us get started with the Postorbital insertion check. Open the Mission pad and find the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > POST INSERTION, and RUN it.
Starting checklist
Apollo 13, Houston. I have your Z torqueing angle. You ready?
Jack is ready to copy, Joe.
Okay. It's plus decimal 26. Over.
Okay, Joe. Plus 0.26.
That's Roger.
So the next item is the SM RCS Monitoring check. Go ahead and RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > SM RCS CHECK checklist in the Mission Pad.
Ok, item 5, the SM RCS CHECK - complete the checklist.
Apollo 13, Houston.
Go ahead, Houston.

Okay. Couple minutes to LOS, Jim. Everything is looking real good. Your AOS time at Carnarvon will be 52:36, and we don't have too much of a handle on why the inboard cut off early except that it apparently was an engine problem and not a switch select function. But we're certain that you'll be able to make TLI based on what we're looking at now.
Roger. There's nothing like an interesting launch.
That's right.
Apollo 13, Houston. Canary LOS in 30 seconds. Request COMMAND RESET, please.
Roger. COMMAND RESET coming on.
Thank you.
Apollo 13, Houston. Request Low Bit Rate, please. Over.
Low Bit Rate.
Let us get started with the next item, that is the CM RCS Monitoring check. RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > CM RCS CHECK checklist.
Can you give me the data of CM 1?
Okay, number 1. Helium temperature is about 80, helium pressure is 4100, and the manifold pressure is about 100.
Manifold's about 100. Okay. Complete the checklist.
Okay, Freddo. Have a look, how is the cabin and suit doing?
They're both pretty equal, now, at about 5/5.
Well, let's fetch the PGA bags for our helmet and gloves.
Okay, let's do it. Freddo, here's your bag.
Okay. Jim.
Okay. Starting with the next item. RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION - C/W OPERATIONAL CHECK, and complete the checklist.
The next item is item 7, the C/W OPERATIONAL CHECK. Will complete.
I've checked the caution and warning. We're up - we're up to item 8.
How we doing time line?
We're a little behind, but it's the kind of stuff that we can catch up lickety-split with.
Okay.
Let me quickly complete item 13. RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > POST INSERTION [13] checklist.
Okay. Let me get - make sure I got this item. I want A, Simplex. Hell, it was already there. B to Off. No, it wasn't. It's just a hard switch again. They really fake you out, these switches...
Yes. I've noticed...
...they move so hard.
I've noticed that, Fred. [Complete the checklist]
Compared with the simulator these switches are so stiff. Okay, let me check item 13 off; I've completed that one. Let's see.
Yes. I've got item 8 next. Let me get down.
Jack, be careful in your movements now, they might trigger motion sickness.
Yes. I'm not having any problems so far.
Okay.
...PCM Bit Rate is Low. I did the Command Reset in Normal. I'll do it again, just to make sure. I have an A, Simplex, and B, Off. That's great. ...
Well, gentlemen, I'll break out my two gold pens.
The longest Napierian trajectory in the world.
Yes. We had - I had a long boost ride, didn't we?
Man!
Twelve minutes and 30 some seconds.
I'll tell you, gang, I was a little worried for a pinch or two.
When I called, 'Inboard,' I was - It was natural; then I looked at the time...
Yes...
..and I said, 'That's not natural.'
We were 2 minutes early. Five minutes and 32 seconds, if you want to write that down.
Okay, good.
Okay, I'm ready for the main Reg check, Fred, if you're ready. [RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > MAIN REG CHECK cl]
Okay. Go ahead.
Okay. Main Reg B going closed. Emergency Cabin Pressure selector 1, Push To Test.
Okay, that's good. Complete the checklist.
Ok, looked good.
Man, I'll tell you, that first stage... When that shut down, man, I thought I was going through the instrument panel. I'll tell you, that was - I was so surprised even I had heard about it.
I should have warned you.
Hahah
Yes. Yes, I can feel a little bit of the zero-g effect, a little flushing in the face.
Yes.
Yes, that's that - Your blood rushes to your head because your heart doesn't have anything to pump against.
Yes, I can feel that, too.
Okay, Jim, let's start with item 12, the ECS config. Are you ready to get busy on getting the RADs on the line?
I sure am.
Glycol Reservoir Bypass valve, Open.
Okay, Glycol Reservoir Bypass valve to Open.
Okay, Out valve, Close.
Out valve, Close.
The In valve, Close.
The In valve going Close.
And we got the secondary RAD leak check to go. [RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > SEC RAD LEAK CHECK cl]
That's it on that item - that page; it's done. So we're hanging up here. Let me proceed ahead and see what I can. I can do a purge. There are not any left for another 12 minutes or so.
[RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > FC PURGE CHECK cl]
Okay, you may - you may get some Master Alarms here, gang. I'm going to be doing a purge check. [Complete the checklist]
When did we insert, gang? Twelve something?
Okay. I'm looking for where I put the first line heater on, so it was roughly about 14 minutes. We've been - we've been 20 minutes.
Don't forget I still got the radiators bypassed here.

Yes. Okay, what I need though, Jim, is to - We got to pump up the - You want to - Let's finish that item. I need to pump up the accumulator a little bit. I mean use the accumulator to - Yes - to get it up to 50 percent.
Can you reach the Prim Accum Fill valve, right there on your left?
Okay. Coming On.
Good. That's good, let me look a minute, here; I have to stabilize. I only need about 5 percent; I don't need much.
Okay, how's that?
It's right at 50, though; the hell with it, that's good. Off.
ECS RAD Control; let me go to Power.
Okay, PRIM Glycol To RADs out, Jim; Normal, push - Normal, push in.
Okay.
Ok, that completes item 12, the ECS Post Insertion Config steps.
Can I get P52 program start?
Yes. Go ahead. [Key V37E 52E on the DSKY]
I will complete item 24. [RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > OPTICS DUST COVER JETT cl]
Zero to Off, G&N Power Optics, on, up. Optics Mode, Manual. Coupling to Direct, Speed to High. OHC, Max right. Ok, item 24 is complete.
Okay.
I've got a star in the...
Sextant?
..sextant, but I have nothing in the...
Well, it might take a while to do it with the scanning telescope, because your eyes have to get accustomed to it. It might not be where there are stars.
[Complete a P52, REFSMMAT (Option 3). RUN the COMMAND MODULE -> P52 AID: REFSMMAT helper in the AOH - skip the steps that requests you to start P52 as it is already done]
Well, I've got one in the - I've got one in the... [Complete the checklist, feel free note down N71 stars, N05 and N93 in the CREW MEMBERS -> REQUEST PADS -> P52 Form]
Okay, I'm going to go ahead with the secondary loop check.
Okay, Secondary Loop is coming on line, gang; AC-1...
That's that little extra whining you hear, and it's the Secondary Loop.
Okay, I'm on page 2-14; coming up to EPS monitor check... [RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > EPS MON CHECK [15] cl]
Okay, item 15's done. And that makes one outstanding item, and I've got a couple from a few pages back.
We got the secondary - we made the secondary check. That completes item 21.
Ok, I have completed the ORDEAL setup, FDAI1 is now slewed to the ORDEAL in ORB RATE.
I think we ought to be having AOS, gang; we've got...
Houston, how do you read 13?
13, Houston. Loud and clear.
Okay, Joe. Everything is going good. We're proceeding on the time line in good fashion. I've got a P52 done. I can give you the torqueing angles.
I'm ready for them, Jack.
Okay. The star angle difference was all balls. Noun 93: minus 067, minus all balls, plus 0.162. [The star angle difference might differ based on your marking performance]
Ah, well, that sounds marginally acceptable.
For a new CMP, it ain't too bad.
Yeah. Okay, 13. We've got nothing for you at the moment. Everything's looking good. We're looking at your data now.
Ok, complete item 16. [RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > ECS MON CHECK]
Okay, will complete item 16 now.
Great, then complete item 17. [RUN the TIMELINE -> INSERTION > SPS MON CHECK]
Roger, completing item 17.
Apollo 13, Houston. LOS Carnarvon in about 30 seconds. Honeysuckle on the hour, and verify your S-band is up for Honeysuckle. Over.
That's verified.
And, Houston, we're beginning to see a beautiful sunrise here.
Roger that, Jim.
Apollo 13, Houston through Honeysuckle.
Roger, Houston; 13 here. Reading you loud and clear.
Okay. S-band sounds good, Jim.
Okay. 13, Houston. LOS Honeysuckle in about 30 seconds, and we'll see you over the States at 1 plus 28 plus 43.
[This completes this part of the mission, continue the journey in Mission 3]

Title: MISSION 2 - INSERTION
Description: The crew of Apollo 13 is in orbit after a slight issue with engine 5, but are all good. They need to complete the insertion checklists and prepare for TLI.
BriefingText:
Primary objectives:
• to perform selenological inspection, survey, and sampling of
materials in a preselected region of the Fra Mauro formation;
• to deploy and activate an Apollo lunar surface experiments package;
• to further develop human capability to work in the lunar environment; and
• to obtain photographs of candidate exploration sites.
